# docker-compose .env — REQUIRED for `docker compose up`.
#
# Why this file exists
# --------------------
# The compose stack runs the `observability` container as a non-root
# UID and bind-mounts three host directories into it
# (`/spool/runs`, `/hostinfo`, `/audit`). Those host dirs are created
# at mode 0700 by `tools/observability_paths_lib.ts::ensureRoot()`
# and owned by whichever UID ran that init step — i.e. the host
# operator. The container UID must match, or the bind mounts are
# unreadable/unwritable. macOS Docker Desktop's VirtioFS / gRPC-FUSE
# layer does NOT translate UIDs on bind mounts; Linux never has.
#
# Two supported deployment paths
# ------------------------------
# 1) DEFAULT — container runs as the host operator's UID/GID.
#    Generate this file with the one-liner:
#        cd tools/observability_server
#        printf 'OBSERVABILITY_UID=%s\nOBSERVABILITY_GID=%s\n' \
#          "$(id -u)" "$(id -g)" > .env
#    Re-run after `id -u` / `id -g` change.
#
# 2) RT1 ACCEPTANCE PATH — container runs as `starkobs:starkobs`
#    (UID 10001), matching the Phase 2 launchd writer plist's
#    dedicated host user. Once Phase 2 has created that user
#    AND chowned the host bind dirs to 10001:10001, set:
#        OBSERVABILITY_UID=10001
#        OBSERVABILITY_GID=10001
#    The compose `init` sidecar will then chown the named SQLite-index
#    volume `/data` (and the /audit bind) to 10001:10001 on every up
#    so the runtime owns its writable mounts.
#
# Either path satisfies the wing-review fix: the runtime UID and the
# bind-mount ownership are coherent.
#
# `OBSERVABILITY_UID` and `OBSERVABILITY_GID` are REQUIRED. The compose
# file uses `${OBSERVABILITY_UID:?...}` syntax so `docker compose up`
# fails loudly if either is unset — preferable to a silent default
# that produces unreadable bind mounts.

OBSERVABILITY_UID=
OBSERVABILITY_GID=
